claim.claim-text:
A variable-geometry exhaust turbine, comprising:
a nozzle mount including a first surface and a second surface;
a nozzle support including a first end portion and a second end portion, the first end portion being joined to the first surface of the nozzle mount;
a nozzle plate including a first surface and a second surface, the first surface being joined to the second end portion of the nozzle support and supported so as to face the nozzle mount at a distance from the nozzle mount, and the second surface facing an exhaust gas channel through which exhaust gas flows; and
at least one nozzle vane supported rotatably between the nozzle mount and the nozzle plate,
wherein the nozzle support is capable of tilting along a radial direction so as to absorb a relative displacement in the radial direction between the nozzle mount and the nozzle plate due to thermal expansion.

1. A variable-geometry exhaust turbine, comprising:
a nozzle mount including a first surface and a second surface;
a nozzle support including a first end portion and a second end portion, the first end portion being joined to the first surface of the nozzle mount;
a nozzle plate including a first surface and a second surface, the first surface being joined to the second end portion of the nozzle support and supported so as to face the nozzle mount and to be spaced from the nozzle mount, and the second surface facing an exhaust gas channel through which exhaust gas flows; and
at least one nozzle vane supported rotatably between the nozzle mount and the nozzle plate,
wherein the nozzle support includes a mechanism for tilting along a radial direction so as to absorb a relative displacement in the radial direction between the nozzle mount and the nozzle plate due to thermal expansion.
